whereas.text:
Whereas President Obama said, [o]ur common
			 prosperity will be advanced by allowing all humanity—men and women—to reach
			 their full potential;

Whereas, on August 10, 2012, President Obama announced the
			 first interagency Strategy to Prevent and Respond to Gender-based Violence
			 Globally;

Whereas the ability of women to realize their full
			 potential is critical to the ability of a country to achieve strong and lasting
			 economic growth and political and social stability;

Whereas, according to the International Monetary Fund,
			 focusing on the needs and empowerment of women is one of the keys to
			 human development;

Whereas, according to the 2012 World Economic Forum Global
			 Gender Gap Report, reducing gender inequality enhances productivity and
			 economic growth;

Whereas, according to the United Nations, 1 in 3 women
			 around the world has experienced some form of gender-based violence and 1 in 4
			 women has been abused during pregnancy;

Whereas, according to the United Nations Population Fund,
			 1 in 9 girls in developing countries (excluding the People's Republic of China)
			 will be married before the age of 15;

Whereas, according to Save the Children, pregnancy-related
			 complications are a leading cause of death among girls between the ages of 15
			 and 19 in developing countries;
